data.enText: to give money, food, clothes, etc. to sb/sth, especially a charity

data.chText: 他向慈善事业捐款数千英镑。
data.enText: He donated thousands of pounds to charity.
to allow doctors to remove blood or a body organ in order to help sb who needs it

data.chText: 对所有捐献的血都要进行艾滋病病毒和其他传染病病毒检测。
data.enText: All donated blood is tested for HIV and other infections.

simple_means.memory_skill: don 给予 + ate 表动词 → 给出去 → 捐赠

ex.chText: 我们向无家可归的地震幸存者捐献了一笔钱。
ex.enText: We contributed a sum of money to the homeless survivors of the earthquake.

synonyms.bx: 指捐赠钱款、提供帮助等，常和介词 to/towards 连用。

ex.chText: 当地民众排队给地震灾区捐款。
ex.enText: The local people lined up to donate money to the earthquake-hit area.

ex.chText: 他给慈善事业捐款非常慷慨。
ex.enText: He is lavish in donating money to charity.

synonyms.bx: 尤指向个人或组织捐赠钱款。

tr: give to a charity or good cause
example: I donated blood to the Red Cross for the victims of the earthquake
She donates to her favorite charity every month

value.def: If you donate something to a charity or other organization, you give it to them.

example.ex: He frequently donates large sums to charity...
example.tran: 他常常向慈善机构捐赠大笔钱款。
其他人捐赠了一些旧衣服。

example.ex: The silver trophy was donated by a Leicester businessman.
example.tran: 银制奖杯是由一个莱斯特的商人捐赠的。

example.ex: ...the donation of his collection to the art gallery.

value.def: If you donate your blood or a part of your body, you allow doctors to use it to help someone who is ill.

example.ex: ...people who are willing to donate their organs for use after death...
example.tran: 愿意死后捐献器官的人们

example.ex: All donated blood is screened for HIV.
example.tran: 所献血液一律要经过人体免疫缺陷病毒的筛查。
旨在鼓励器官捐献的措施

partsOfSpeech.dec: con 共同 + dit 给予 + ion 表名词 → 共同给出〔前提〕→ 条件
con 加强 + don 给予 + e → 给予〔大度〕→ 原谅
don 给予 + ate 做，造成，使… → 给出去 → 捐赠
don 给予 + or 表人 → 给予的人 → 捐献者
e 出 + dit 给予 → 给出〔好文章〕→ 编辑
en 使… + dow 给予 → 资助；捐赠
extra 向外 + dit 给予 + e → 向外交出〔逃犯〕→ 引渡
par 平等 + don 给予 → 原谅，宽恕
tra〔= trans 转移〕+ dit 给予 + ion 表名词 → 代代相传 → 传统
